Ad Text:
About Us

At Sportsbet, we’re all about bringing excitement to life for our 2.4 million customers. As part of the global Flutter Group, we’re a tight-knit team of 1,300 in Melbourne, Sydney, and Darwin, passionate about challenging the status quo. We’re proud to be recognized as one of LinkedIn’s Top 25 Companies and one of the Top 10 Workplaces for Women. We’re an inclusive employer who celebrates diversity and is committed to helping you thrive. Whether you’re looking for flexibility, career growth, or a supportive environment, we’re here to help you succeed.

Committed To Responsible Gambling

Our commitment to responsible gambling is genuine and demonstrated through the wide range of responsible gambling initiatives and tools. We’re proud to be the leaders in responsible gambling in our industry, not just locally, but globally.

The Team

In Data Science we work collaboratively with teams across the organisation to create and evolve end to end solutions that have Data Science at their core. From sports modelling to product personalisation, our team thrives on unleashing the power of data to improve the quality, speed and complexity of the decisions and actions they drive. Our models not only power many of the products our customers get to enjoy, but they also take many of our internal processes to the next level.

We care for things we have built and look at ways to continuously improve them; but we also love to innovate. We are known pioneers and have introduced a number of world first ML-driven customer-facing products. They come from insights, experience but often, just from someone thinking outside of the box – we play a key role in exploring these ideas and making them a reality. Not only we innovate with product, but also in the way we build, develop, deploy and maintain our solutions and how we leverage evolving platforms partnerships.

The Role

Joining the Customer Growth team, the duties and responsibilities include:

Work with key stakeholders from across the business to ensure that business requirements are explored, understood and considered when designing and building models.
Communicate complex technical information in an easy-to-understand way to keep stakeholders engaged and aligned to progress.
Design and deploy models in accordance with MLOps best principles to deliver high quality and supportable products.
Contribute in designing ways to test, track and communicate the ongoing impact of the solutions we deliver.

You - some of the talents we’re looking to find:

Experience with conceiving, designing, building, deploying and monitoring machine learning models, with an excellent eye for detail.
Commercially minded – track record of unlocking data to drive commercial value.
Broad knowledge of statistical and computational methods for identifying patterns, extracting insights, and making predictions from complex datasets.
Strong programming skills (e.g. proficient in Python, R etc with experience in Spark and Databricks a plus).
Degree in a quantitative discipline (e.g. Mathematics, Statistics, Physics, Computer Science).
Good communication skills with the ability to explain complex concepts to a wide variety of audiences, both verbally and written.

Why You’ll Love Working Here

Along with a competitive salary and generous performance-based bonus, here’s some of our other benefits:
25 days annual leave (plus flexible working options)
$1050 work-from-home allowance
Access to outstanding career development programs, including expert-led internal training and external learning opportunities
Onsite concierge services, free meals, social events and access to the Sportsbet Salon
Generous parental leave and return-to-work benefits
Hack Days: Participate in our hack days, where creativity and collaboration lead to exciting new ideas and projects.

What’s the Green Tick Feeling?

Well, it’s different for everyone, yet unites us all. It’s the feeling you get when you succeed, no matter what success looks like to you. It could be developing your career, it could be working on an industry leading project, or it could be making it to school pick up in time. It's all the little and big things that make you feel like you’re thriving when working at Sportsbet.

We’re an inclusive employer who welcomes you for who you are, as you are – so, if you require adjustments to the recruitment process, please let us know in your application. We also know flex means different things to different people, so let us know how we can support you to be your best.

We review applications quickly, so apply soon! Check out our Life@Sportsbet Instagram, LinkedIn, and careers website for more about our inclusive culture.

Ready for your Green Tick Feeling? Apply now.

Job Title: Data Engineer | AWS | Snowflake | Redshift | DBT
Ad Text:
We are HCLTech, one of the fastest-growing large tech companies in the world and home to 219,000+ people across 54 countries, supercharging progress through industry-leading capabilities centered around Digital, Engineering and Cloud.

The driving force behind that work, our people, are diverse, creative, and passionate, raising the bar for excellence on a regular basis. We, in turn, work hard to bring out the best in them as we strive to help them find their spark and become the best version of themselves that they can be.

Are you ready to be an important part of this ever-transformational journey?

At HCLTech Australia, we value the unique perspective and contributions of all individual and we actively encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people to apply for this role.

Job Role Overview:

Primary Skills - (AWS+RED SHIFT) + DBT + Snowflake

Secondary Skills – Teradata + Snowflake

AWS + Snowflake - Key Responsibilities:

• Understand customer requirements and render those as architectural models that will operate at large scale and high performance. Where customers have architectures prepared, validate them against non-functional requirements and finalize the build model.

• Experience in creating and monitoring SNOW PIPE for continuous data ingestion from source.

• Experience in Loading data into snowflake tables from the internal stage using Snow SQL (CLI)

• Work alongside customers to build data management platforms using AWS products like Elastic Map Reduce (EMR), Redshift, Kinesis, Amazon Machine Learning, Amazon Athena, Lake Formation, S3, AWS Glue, DynamoDB, ElastiCache and the Relational Database Service (RDS)

• Hands on experience in Python.

• Well experience on other AWS services EC2, EMR, Redshift, S3, Streaming services like Kafka, Kinesis, HDFS.

• Experience in AWS + Snowflake/Redshift implementation is must.

• Security of EMR cluster using KMS keys or customer managed keys

• Deep experience on Snowflakes/AWS native data services including Glue, Glue Catalog, EMR, PySpark-EMR, Data Sync, RDS, Data Exchange, Lake Formation, Athena, Apache Airflow and dbt.

• (Secondary) Knowledge on Teradata SQL, Teradata Utilities – TPT, FASTLOAD, MLOAD, FASTEXPORT, TPUMP and Scripting - Bteq & Unix shell scripting

• (Secondary) Knowledge of database technologies Teradata, DataStage, Cloudera, Big data Hadoop

• Render working, high performance data management solutions, as CloudFormation and reusable artifacts for implementation by the customer. Bootstrap using user data scripts will be added advantage

• Prepare architecture and design briefs that outline the key features and decision points of the application built in the Data Lab

• Work with customers to advise on changes as they put these systems live on AWS

• Extract best-practice knowledge, reference architectures, and patterns from these engagements for sharing with the worldwide AWS solution architect community




Basic Qualifications:

· 5 to 10 years of IT experience with 5+ years of experience in Data Engineering and 5+ years of hands-on experience in Snowflake Data/AWS Services (e.g. S3, Glue, Glue Catalog, Lake Formation)

· Strong understanding of Snowflake architecture.

· Strong understanding of Teradata or DataStage architecture. (Secondary)

· Experience with data migration tools like Glue, Data Sync.

· Excellent knowledge of data modeling, data warehousing, ETL processes, and other Data management systems.

· Strong understanding of security and compliance requirements in cloud.

· Experience in Agile development methodologies and version control systems.

· Excellent communication an leadership skills. Ability to work effectively across internal and external organizations and virtual teams.

· AWS Certified Data Analytics – Specialty.

· Experience on Containerization and serverless computing.

· Familiarity with DevOps practices and automation tools.







Preferred Qualifications:

· Technical degrees in computer science, software engineering, or mathematics

· Cloud and Data Engineering background with Migration experience.




Other Skills:

· A critical thinker with strong research, analytics and problem-solving skills

· Self-motivated with a positive attitude and an ability to work independently and or in a team

· Able to work under tight timeline and deliver on complex problems.

· Must be able to work flexible hours (including weekends and nights) as needed.

· A strong team player







Why Us

We are one of the fastest-growing large tech companies in the world, with offices in 50+ countries across the globe and 219,000 employees.

Our company is extremely diverse with 165 nationalities represented.

We offer the opportunity to work with colleagues across the globe.

We offer a virtual-first work environment, promoting a good work-life integration and real flexibility.

We offer comprehensive benefits for all employees.

We are a certified great place to work and a top employer in 17 countries, offering a positive work environment that values employee recognition and respect.

Equality & Opportunity for All

Representing 165 nationalities across the globe, we pride ourselves on being an equal opportunity employer, committed to providing equal employment opportunities to all applicants and employees regardless of race, religion, sex, color, age, national origin, pregnancy, sexual orientation, physical disability or genetic information, military or veteran status, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people or any other protected classification, in accordance with federal, state, and/or local law.

Candidate Data Privacy Notice | HCL Technologies

We are committed to respecting your privacy and for the protection of your personal data. Your personal data will be collected and processed in line with our candidate privacy notice: https://www.hcltech.com/candidate-privacy-notice. This privacy notice will help you to understand what personal data we collect about you, how we use this personal data, and what rights you have regarding your personal data.  By replying to this email or submitting any personal data to HCLTech, you acknowledge that you have read and understood the candidate privacy notice and  have  provided your consent to the processing of your data for recruitment purposes as described in the privacy notice”.

We are seeking a Data Engineer / Scientist (Healthcare Analytics) to lead the charge in designing and delivering innovative, scalable data solutions that power secure data management and advanced analytics across the health sector. In this pivotal role, you will drive a landmark data linkage project connecting general practice and hospital data—unlocking insights that enable smarter, evidence-based decisions. Your work will transform health outcomes not only for the Gold Coast community but across Queensland, improving the health system at scale.

About Us

Gold Coast Primary Health Network (GCPHN) is an independent, not-for-profit company, one of 31 Primary Health Networks established by the Australian Government. We identify the health needs of our local community, then fund and improve primary health services to keep people well and out of hospital. GCPHN is building ‘one world-class health system for the Gold Coast’ and we know we can’t do it alone.

What We Offer

Remuneration package of $134,367 - $148,824 + Super
Flexible work arrangements that support work-life balance, including access to remote or hybrid working policy, with the requirement to travel to the office as needed
Salary packaging (Fringe Benefit Tax exemptions) up to $15,900 p.a. + $2,650 p.a. meal and entertainment (tax-free income)
Exceptional organisational reputation with established relationships in primary health care
Additional benefits of 5 weeks of annual leave per year, paid parental leave, plus annual CPI salary increases
Benchmarked 'Soaring' workplace culture, with a supportive and collaborative team
Convenient location at Robina (Gold Coast) with free onsite parking

About the Role

As the Data Engineer / Scientist, you will play a key role in transforming how health data is collected, linked, and analysed to support strategic decision-making and improve health outcomes. Working within a centralised Azure-based data infrastructure, you will lead the development of data pipelines, implement privacy-preserving record linkage, and apply advanced analytics and machine learning techniques to generate actionable insights.

You will play a pivotal role in delivering secure, scalable data solutions that power innovation across the Gold Coast and influence statewide and national initiatives. Collaborating closely with internal teams and external partners, you will drive projects that not only transform integrated care locally but set the standard for health outcomes across Queensland. This is your opportunity to make a lasting impact—regionally and beyond.

Key Responsibilities

Design and maintain scalable data engineering solutions using Microsoft Azure tools (Synapse, Fabric, Data Factory)
Lead the linkage of general practice and hospital data using Privacy Preserving Record Linkage (PPRL)
Develop and optimise ETL pipelines and integrate APIs to support robust data workflows
Apply machine learning and AI techniques to support predictive modelling and advanced analytics
Build and maintain Power BI dashboards and productivity tools to support data-driven decision-making
Ensure data governance, privacy, and security standards are upheld (e.g., ISO27001, FHIR)
Collaborate with cross-functional teams and communicate complex data insights to non-technical stakeholders
Support analytics maturity uplift across the organisation and contribute to strategic projects

Eligibility Criteria

Essential:

Tertiary qualifications in Data Science, Computer Science, Information Systems, Software Engineering, Statistics, or a related discipline
Minimum 3 years’ experience managing and optimising data repositories within the Microsoft Azure ecosystem
Strong experience with ETL tools (Azure Data Factory, Synapse, Fabric) and API integration
Demonstrated expertise in privacy-preserving data linkage and healthcare data environments
Advanced proficiency in SQL and database design
Experience with Power BI and scripting (e.g., PowerShell)
Familiarity with ISO27001, FHIR standards, and privacy legislation
Excellent communication skills with the ability to present complex data to diverse audiences
Strong organisational and project management skills

Desirable:

Azure certification (e.g., Azure Data Engineer Associate)
Proficiency in Python, R, DAX, Java, or C# Experience in primary health care or epidemiological data analysis

How to Apply

To apply, please submit a cover letter addressing the selection criteria along with your current resume. Your cover letter should include specific examples that demonstrate your relevant experience, knowledge, and capabilities for the role.

Applications close Thursday 27th November at 9:00am.

Please note that the successful candidate will be required to undergo National Police Clearance.

I-MED Radiology Network is Australia's largest and a global leader of diagnostic imaging, with circa 5,000 employees, located in more than 240 clinics across metropolitan, regional, and rural communities throughout Australia. We offer medical imaging and radiology services including x-ray, PET, CT, MRI, Nuclear Medicine, Ultrasound, Mammography and interventional procedures and each year across the network we perform more than 5 million patient procedures.

About The Role

We're looking for a Solution Architect with a hands-on approach to join our development team and help design and implement innovative solutions in the healthcare space. While your primary focus will be on architecting solutions in AWS, you'll also roll up your sleeves and assist the team with building and delivering these solutions.

Our core technology stack includes AWS, Java, Python, and PostgreSQL, with opportunities to work across other platforms and solutions within the business. You'll join an established team where your expertise will influence technical direction and ensure robust, scalable, and secure architectures.

You'll bring a positive, collaborative, and forward-thinking mindset, with a passion for delivering high-quality solutions and supporting both internal and external stakeholders.

Key Accountabilities:


Design and document AWS-based solution architectures aligned with business requirements and best practices.
Collaborate with stakeholders to translate business needs into technical designs.
Assist in hands-on development, testing, and deployment of software solutions.
Participate in code reviews, agile ceremonies, and contribute to continuous improvement initiatives.
Provide technical leadership, mentor team members, and guide best practices in cloud architecture and development.
Identify opportunities for automation, scalability, and performance improvements across the solution landscape.

Key selection criteria:


Proven experience as a Solution Architect with strong AWS expertise (including services such as Lambda, API Gateway, ECS/EKS, RDS, S3, IAM).
Solid development experience with Java and/or Python and related frameworks.
Familiarity with front-end frameworks (e.g., React) is advantageous.
Strong understanding of RESTful API design and integration.
Competent with PostgreSQL and relational database design.
Experience with modern architectures: microservices, serverless, containerization.
Ability to balance high-level design with hands-on implementation.
Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills.
Strong communication skills, both written and verbal.
AWS Certification or related IT architecture certification desirable.
Knowledge of healthcare IT standards (HL7, DICOM) is beneficial.
Exposure to AI/ML solution implementation is a plus.

What can I-MED offer you?


Supportive and professional working environment in our brand-new head office(s)
Opportunity to work within a large-scaled and advanced technology environment
Commitment to your health and well-being with access to our employee assistance program. I-MED's Lifeworks portal gives employees access to a number of resources, plus exclusive offers on everyday purchases from well-known companies
Strong commitment to continual professional development
Flexible work arrangements and a hybrid work model
A competitive remuneration package plus a range of employee benefits such as free parking (Melbourne office), paid parental leave, salary packaging options, discounted health insurance and gym memberships, banking, and travel benefits and much more

At I-MED we have an all-inclusive culture that puts our patients at the foremost of everything we do. As a diverse group of professionals, we are committed to working together as one team to make a real difference in the lives of our patients. Our positive working environment and hybrid work policy promotes flexibility and work/life balance. We believe the quality of our people, state-of-the art systems and technology, and imaging and diagnosis, sets us apart.

If you're seeking an opportunity to join a growing healthcare business, in a role that offers fast-paced, interesting and varied work, we encourage you to apply today.

Software Engineer (AI Systems)

LabNext70

2 x Fixed term positions, full-time up to 12 months

Armidale based role. Flexible or hybrid work arrangements available

Current UNE Staff: In taking up this appointment, please be aware your current fixed term or permanent role will cease the day prior to you taking this position

$ 110,591 to $ 128,345 per annum HEO8

Plus 17% employer superannuation

Salary packaging options are available

20 days family and domestic violence leave available per annum

10 days Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander cultural and ceremonial leave per annum

5 weeks annual leave plus Christmas week shutdown, per annum

Applicants must have appropriate Australian work rights for the duration of this position (UNE will not provide sponsorship for this position)

Acknowledgement of Country

The University of New England (UNE) is a regionally based, globally networked university renowned for the quality of its student experience and the excellence of its research specialisations. In addition, UNE pioneered teaching to external students making it the most experienced provider of distance and innovative online education. UNE emphasises its people, staff and students' growth and development. We aspire to be a leader in innovation and change and a centre for the Armidale and the North-West communities. Equity, diversity and inclusion are central to the core values of UNE and we are committed to engaging, supporting and growing a richly diverse workforce. From the Oorala Aboriginal Centre at the heart of our campus, to the inclusive organisations such as the UNE Ally Network, the UNE Women’s Society, and the many international cultural groups - all will feel valued and respected at UNE. You will embody the UNE values and strive to be Open, Enquiring, Exceptional and Making a Difference. Additionally, you will be committed to achieving the goals embedded in the Future Fit Strategic Plan 2021-2030.

About the role

The Software Engineer (AI Systems) is responsible for designing, building, and implementing complex software systems that support LabNext70's and the University's operational and strategic objectives. You will design and build software applications using AI/ML frameworks, cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP), and containerisation technologies (Docker, Kubernetes). Leading technical architecture and design, you'll develop specifications for major projects and create enterprise-level APIs, microservices, and distributed system components. Your work will include implementing CI/CD pipelines, automated testing frameworks, and infrastructure as code. You'll solve complex technical problems, build proof-of-concepts to validate approaches, and research emerging technologies. Providing technical support to project teams and creating documentation will be key aspects of the role.

About you

To be successful in this role, you will have:

Expert-level programming and development skills across multiple languages (such as Python, Java, C#, JavaScript/TypeScript, Go) with extensive experience building production-grade applications

Strong cloud and infrastructure expertise including cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or GCP), containerisation (Docker, Kubernetes), infrastructure as code, and CI/CD pipeline implementation

Proven system architecture capabilities to design and build complex, scalable systems including microservices, distributed architectures, APIs, and database solutions

Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills with ability to tackle complex technical challenges, research emerging technologies, and develop innovative solutions

Strong communication and collaboration abilities to work effectively with stakeholders, translate business requirements into technical solutions, and deliver quality outcomes independently

About the Faculty/Group

LabNext70 is UNE's hub for AI innovation, where cutting-edge technology meets education. We're focused on transforming teaching and learning, improving operational efficiency, and exploring bold new ideas for the future of education. Working with partners across industry, government, and the community, we're pioneering AI-driven solutions that make a real difference. LabNext70 currently has an exciting opportunity for an experienced Software Engineer (AI Systems) to join our innovative team. This role offers the chance to work at the forefront of AI technology in higher education, designing and building complex software systems that drive innovation across the University. You'll work with cutting-edge technologies including AI/ML frameworks, cloud platforms, and modern development practices to create scalable solutions that enhance educational experiences and operational effectiveness. This is an opportunity to make a tangible impact while working in a collaborative, forward-thinking environment that values technical excellence and innovation.

About Armidale

Armidale is an attractive and vibrant city that combines all the features of a bustling regional town centre with the tranquillity of rural living. It boasts gourmet restaurants and cafes, boutique shopping, quality schools and sporting facilities. Surrounded by mountain gorges, waterfalls and national parks, Armidale’s natural beauty and distinct seasons make it an ideal place to live and thrive. To find out more, visit https://www.visitarmidale.com.au/experience

Enquiries and additional information

To discuss this role please contact Connor Ventura, AI Engineering Manager – LabNext70, phone: 02 6773 5109 email: cventur2@une.edu.au. 

Closing Date: Midnight, 23 November 2025

Reference No:   225166

Please visit www.une.edu.au/jobs-at-une for further information about this position and other career opportunities at UNE.

To Apply

Submit your application through www.une.edu.au/jobs-at-une and refer to vacancy ref 225166

Your application should be comprised of:

Covering letter addressing applicant’s suitability for the position based on key functions of the role detailed in the Position Description.

Current CV.

Commitment to Inclusion and Diversity

UNE is committed to building a diverse workforce and strongly encourage applications from Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander Australians, people with disability, people from diverse cultural and linguistic backgrounds, mature age workers and LGBTQIA+ people. 

About Our Process

At UNE, we are committed to employing individuals who meet the requirements of this role and align with our values. All applicants will be contacted and advised of an outcome. The successful candidate will be required to undertake pre-employment checks prior to commencing in this role as indicated in the position statement. Please visit our Privacy Statement to understand how your information is collected, stored, accessed and used.

National Police Check

If you are the successful candidate for this role you will be required to provide UNE with a National Police Check prior to your commencement. Please note that people with criminal records are NOT automatically barred from applying for this position (unless there is a particular requirement under law).

Senior Solution Engineer – Applied AI Systems

The team develops advanced systems such as intelligent automation, agent frameworks and enterprise knowledge solutions using the latest model APIs and orchestration platforms.

Key Responsibilities
Lead architecture, design and delivery of scalable AI systems
Set technical standards and ensure reliability, security and quality
Oversee engineering decisions and code review across multiple projects
Work directly with senior stakeholders to translate requirements into solutions
Support and coach engineers to raise capability and delivery pace
Contribute to R&D and reusable components that accelerate future builds
You Will Bring
Strong background in software or data engineering with hands-on delivery experience
Deep knowledge of LLMs, vector databases, embeddings and model orchestration tools
Expertise in microservice design, API integration and data pipelines
Proven record leading teams building production-grade applications
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills
Proactive mindset, self-sufficiency and attention to technical quality
Why This Opportunity
Lead high-value projects using cutting-edge model technology
Join an elite engineering team working with world-class partners
Competitive salary, share options and full benefits package
Hybrid working model with flexibility for key client delivery
